DURING A TOWED TAKE OFF, THE TOW PLANE LOST ENGINE POWER AND THE TOW 
PILOT RELEASED THE GLIDER. THE GLIDER PILOT ALSO RELEASED THE TOW LINE, 
THEN BEGAN A LEFT TURN TO PROVIDE ENOUGH ROOM TO MAKE A RIGHT TURN 
BACK TO THE RUNWAY. HE STATED THAT, DURING THE RIGHT TURN BACK TO THE 
RUNWAY, THE NOSE FELL AND THE GLIDER IMPACTED THE GROUND. 
The pilot's attempted return to the departure runway that resulted in a stall at an altutude that 
was too low to permit recovery. 
